There was a fire outbreak at Agbeni Market in Ibadan on Monday, leading to the loss of goods worth several millions of naira.  It was gathered that the incident occurred in the early hours of the day. It was gathered that the incident occurred at the Jamoje compound in Agbeni market. Traders in the market reportedly made several efforts to put out the fire to no avail. About four shops were affected by the inferno before help came. Sources told Dailypost that goods worth millions of naira were destroyed before the fire was extinguished. Head of Oyo state fire service, Mr. Mashood Adewuyi, confirmed the incident to DAILY POST, explaining that the fire was noticed in the early hours of the day. He said, “Yes. The incident occurred. “It occurred this morning”.  Source Ilorin - A midnight inferno on Sunday consumed goods worth millions of naira at Baboko market in Ilorin, the Kwara capital. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that 20 shops were completely razed by the inferno which lasted several hours. NAN gathered that some shop owners left huge sums… In "News" Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  The Government of Oyo State said on Sunday that it was set to acquire 10 modern fire-fighting equipment through a competitive bidding process. The State's Commissioner for Infrastructure, Transportation and Public Works, Professor Raphael Afonja, who made the disclosure while undertaking an on-the-spot assessment of the… In "News" By Moji Eniola   Ojota   -      Fire gutted a section of Binukonu Ultra Modern Market, Ojota in Lagos in the early hours of Friday, destroying goods and property worth millions of Naira. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that this was the third fire incident at… In "News"